id: pm-vi2v
title: Add governance normalize command with dry-run and apply modes
description: Implement a first-class pm command that detects low-signal metadata patterns and optionally applies deterministic normalization updates with auditable mutation plans.
type: Feature
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[4]: automation,governance,normalization,pm-cli
created_at: "2026-04-04T21:55:02.727Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-17T08:22:53.002Z"
deadline: "2026-05-09T17:10:36.281Z"
author: codex-agent
estimated_minutes: 300
acceptance_criteria: "A governance normalize command can (1) scan and report placeholder/low-signal metadata patterns, (2) emit deterministic mutation previews, and (3) apply approved updates while preserving history and ownership semantics."
definition_of_ready: Pattern catalog and replacement policies are captured from completed governance sweeps.
goal: Governance operations by default
objective: Replace manual metadata normalization scripts
value: Reduces manual command volume and inconsistent cleanup outcomes
impact: Improves repeatability and lowers operational error risk
outcome: Agents can run governance normalization from a supported pm command
why_now: Recent sweep required >400 scripted metadata mutations that should be productized.
parent: pm-5rjn
reviewer: maintainer-review
risk: medium
confidence: medium
sprint: governance-followups
release: vnext
reporter: codex-agent
severity: medium
environment: linux
repro_steps: Attempt full metadata normalization on tracker without custom scripts and observe missing command support.
resolution: "Implemented pm normalize command with lifecycle drift detection, deterministic plan output, and guarded apply execution backed by update semantics."
expected_result: Normalize command supports dry-run/apply modes with command/help/contracts/completion/Pi parity and targeted unit+integration coverage.
actual_result: "All targeted normalize/parity tests passed, integration readiness suites passed, and linked pm test run completed successfully with build/typecheck verification."
affected_version: 2026.3.12
component: governance-normalize
regression: false
customer_impact: Maintainers and agents can perform consistent tracker normalization with less manual overhead.
comments[3]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-04-04T21:55:02.727Z",codex-agent,"Duplicate-check evidence: pm search 'automated standards alignment metadata normalization command' --limit 20; pm search 'bulk governance normalization command pm tracker' --limit 20; pm list-open --limit 20. Net-new because existing items capture manual execution history,not a dedicated normalize command surface."
  "2026-04-27T20:10:34.789Z",codex-agent,"Execution scope 2026-04-27 (mixed-wave): implement first-class normalize command in two slices. Slice A (dry-run): detect low-signal metadata/closure-like drift patterns and emit deterministic mutation previews sorted by item id/field, reusing governance policy primitives from validate and update-many planning semantics. Slice B (apply): execute approved normalization updates via safe mutation flow with explicit apply flag, preserving ownership semantics/history writes and avoiding non-deterministic side effects. Acceptance mapping: (1) scan/report = normalized findings + per-item planned field changes and summary counts; (2) deterministic preview = stable dry-run output contract suitable for agent automation (--json); (3) apply mode = history-backed updates through existing PM mutation pathways with clear result reporting and warnings."
  "2026-04-27T20:47:18.552Z",codex-agent,"Delivered pm normalize as a first-class governance command with deterministic dry-run planning and explicit apply mode. Coverage includes core command implementation + main wiring, contracts/completion/help surfaces, Pi wrapper action mapping, and docs updates across README/ARCHITECTURE/AGENTS/CHANGELOG. Linked verification passed via pm test pm-vi2v --run --progress (integration help+release-readiness, normalize/completion/contracts/pi unit suites, validate command suite, and pnpm -s build). Additional repository-wide checks were run for close readiness: pm validate --check-resolution --check-history-drift --json and pm health --check-only --json; warnings were limited to pre-existing out-of-scope items (resolution gaps on historical closed IDs, history drift for pm-r9ei/pm-vhdc, telemetry queue pending entries, and vectorization stale item pm-k8i0)."
notes[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-04-04T21:55:02.727Z",codex-agent,"Design should support audit-only mode first,then explicit apply mode with deterministic ordering and change summaries."
  "2026-04-27T20:10:38.999Z",codex-agent,"Implementation reuse map: parser/help wiring in src/cli/main.ts and help-content.ts; detection/policy borrowing from src/cli/commands/validate.ts lifecycle+metadata checks; preview/apply orchestration patterns from src/cli/commands/update-many.ts with runUpdate-backed mutation execution."
